New Zealand goods and services tax (NZ GST) at 15% is applicable to cross-border remote services and intangibles supplied by non-resident suppliers to person resident in New Zealand unless the person is a GST-registered business. A supplier must treat the recipient as not being a registered person unless the recipient notifies the supplier that they are a registered person and provides their NZ GST registration number.
In this connection, please provide the NZ GST registration number of your entity. If otherwise, NZ GST at 15% may be chargeable on our supply to you.
If there is any change to your entity's NZ GST registration number or if your entity subsequently deregisters for GST in New Zealand, please inform us immediately.
